    "This suggests a climatic control of plant-soilmicrobial interactions 75, particularly in more extreme environments, and has implications for predicting the response of plant-soil systems to environmental change factors.",
    "We have presented extensive evidence that DSE potentially shape the structure and function of root and soil microbiomes via root colonization rates.",
    "However, DSE as a fungal guild of investigation is ambiguous.",
    "The taxonomy and phylogenetic breadth of fungi forming DSE associations is poorly understood 76, there is no highly curated database specifically for DSE taxa, and DSE are usually assigned at the strain level.",
    "Furthermore, the ecology and functioning of DSE is obscure 25, 26, with cryptic lifestyles often closely associated with EcM, AM, and ericoid mycorrhizal associations on woody plants, and they may form different associations on different hosts, reflecting structural and functional flexibility [77] [78] [79] [80]."
